{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n\n`src/rebar/_commands/composer.py` (~line 112) validates titles with `if not title:`,\nwhich is falsy only for the empty string — a whitespace-only title such as `\"   \"` is\ntruthy and is accepted. Per the decision for this epic, whitespace-only titles must be\nrejected. Separately, cross-facade parity tests use only simple ASCII values, and the\ncreate path's empty/`>255` title rejection has code enforcement but only an edit-path\ntest, leaving input-handling contracts thinly covered.\n\n## What\n\n- Reject whitespace-only titles (trim then check non-empty) consistently across the\n  CLI, library, and MCP create/edit surfaces.\n- Add a create-path test for empty and `>255`-char title rejection.\n- Add a curated cross-facade text corpus for values representable through all three\n  facades; handle argv-impossible values (NUL) in library/MCP tests only.\n\n## Scope\n\n- `src/rebar/_commands/composer.py` (title validation)\n- `tests/interfaces/facades/` (corpus + create-path validation tests)\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] A whitespace-only title (spaces/tabs/newlines) is rejected on create AND edit\n      across CLI, library, and MCP, with a clear error.\n- [ ] Create-path tests assert rejection of an empty title and a `>255`-char title.\n- [ ] A shared corpus (leading `-`/`--`, quotes, backslashes, LF/CRLF, emoji/non-BMP,\n      composed vs decomposed Unicode as separate preservation cases, moderately large\n      text) round-trips identically or is rejected identically across all three facades;\n      persisted/replayed content and structured output are asserted, with no\n      stdout/stderr contamination.\n- [ ] NUL / other argv-impossible values are covered via library/MCP tests only.\n- [ ] Breaking-change handling: this is a user-visible tightening (callers passing\n      whitespace previously succeeded). Document a back-out/expand-contract note, and\n      confirm whether any stored tickets have whitespace-only titles (a one-off store\n      scan) so no migration is silently required.\n- [ ] User-facing docs updated: CLI help text / API reference and a CHANGELOG entry\n      note the new whitespace-title rejection.\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783887514276968001,"uuid":"97ef1f4a-163c-4552-8559-eb346e6d1e01"}